Sentencas: Tocheck the suitability of La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.85Mg0.15O3-delta-Ag cermets as cathode material for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) with Sr- and Mg-doped LaGaO3 electrolyte a series of cermets with different Ag contents were prepared by conventional sintering process.
Titulo: Cermet cathodes for strontium and magnesium-doped LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The chemical compatibility between La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.85Mg0.15O3-delta (LSGM) and Ag was investigated by X-ray diffraction, scanning electron microscopy, and X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy.
Titulo: Cermet cathodes for strontium and magnesium-doped LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Thermal expansion coefficient of the cermets was measured as a function of Ag content and was found to increase with increasing metallic content.
Titulo: Cermet cathodes for strontium and magnesium-doped LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Oxygen adsorption at the surface of the cermets could be detected but no reaction or solid solubility between LSGM and Ag was found.
Titulo: Cermet cathodes for strontium and magnesium-doped LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It was noticed that a minimum of 30 wt.% Ag is needed to form a cermet with percolating network.
Titulo: Cermet cathodes for strontium and magnesium-doped LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: From impedance spectroscopy measurement activation energy for the polarization conductance was found to be around 110 kJ mol(-1).
Titulo: Cermet cathodes for strontium and magnesium-doped LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cells
